LAGOS  – The Ogun State Special Adviser/Director General, Bureau of Land and Survey, Mr. Aina Salami, has said that over 4,000 Certificate of Occupancy had been issued to land owners who registered for the last scheme tagged “Ogun Homeowners’ Charter” (HOC) under the new scheme, called Ogun State Land Administration and Revenue Management System (OLARMS). Salami made this known at a town hall meeting held with the residents of Aiyetoro, Lukosi, Seidu, Ilara, Semawa, Imagbon, Aguntoye, Konigbagbe and its environs, held at Ogijo, Sagamu Local Government Area of the State. He said the programme which was peculiar and would make the State and residents value the land resources at their disposal through ratification of their land and property documents, adding that apparently people had been encroaching on government lands, but not intending to demolish their structures, but give them land settlement through ratification. LASG Monthly Rental Scheme To Take-Off Soon – Awoyinka Teczo Real Estate Has Been A Profitable Option -Obaego “Indeed, the programme is an amnesty for those who built on acquisition land, which the government not intended to demolish but will be able get their title document through ratification at a subsidized rate”, he said He pointed out, that the present administration didn’t jettison the previous scheme in giving those who applied for CofO through HOC, saying that the Bureau were facing challenges of contacting those whorequested for the title documents. He said that tracing those who applied for the scheme was very difficult, as most of their numbers used to register for the documents could not be reached, while their emails had been dead. He said that the government iwas doing everything humanly possible to alleviate poverty among its citizens through the introduction of the scheme, adding that it offered them some opportunities to get their land title documents with ease and through digitization.